                <head>No. 84.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to General <persName
                            type="to">Schenck</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-06-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 2, 1872</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Confidential. We concur in the opinion that the Arbitrators have the power to
                    adjourn either on their own motion or on the motion of either party.</p>
                <p>If the arguments be put in on both sides on 15th, and Great Britain move for an
                    adjournment, this Government will concur.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
